Pronotum. Transverse (PWmax/PL = 
1.41–1.50
), widest at beginning of second third, markedly narrowed basad (PWmax/PWmin = 
1.20–1.26
). Sides gently rounded anteriorly, distinctly sinuate in basal third, each with one setigerous pore in widest point; lateral bead not widened basally. Apical margin rather shallowly emarginate, bordered only laterally. Basal border nearly straight, at most somewhat rounded just at basal angles, distinctly bordered throughout, about as long as apical margin and noticeably shorter than elytral base between humeral angles. Apical angles acute, slightly protruded anteriad, blunt at apices. Basal angles right or obtuse, rather sharp at apices, without denticles. Pronotal disc moderately convex, slightly sloped towards basal angles and markedly so towards apical angles. Lateral furrows narrow up to basal angles, lateral depressions absent. Basal foveae small, oval or somewhat elongate, not deep, separated from lateral furrows and basal pronotal margin by convexities. Area between basal foveae slightly convex. Base of pronotum irregularly and vaguely punctate.

Ventral side. Prosternum covered with short setae anteriorly; prosternal process not projected posteriad. Proepisterna (propleura) nearly smooth, at most vaguely micro-punctate anteriorly. Metepisterna (
Fig. 54
) transverse, markedly wider than long, somewhat narrowed posteriad. Sternum VII (last visible) in both sexes with two pairs of setae along apical margin and rounded at apex.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 55
). Laterotergite IX very small, transverse; apical stylomere short and wide.

Aedeagus. Median lobe (
Fig. 53
) bent ventrad behind basal bulb, slightly curved dorsad just at apex, with sides rounded in medial portion and markedly converging in apical portion. Terminal lamella very short, obtuse at apex, without apical capitulum. Apical orifice in dorsal position, prolonged to basal bulb. Internal sac without any distinct sclerotized elements.
